Certainly! Below is a simple Perl script that reverses a given string:

```perl
#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;

# Function to reverse a string
sub reverse_string {
    my ($string) = @_;
    return scalar reverse $string;
}

# Main program
print "Enter a string to reverse: ";
my $input = <STDIN>;
chomp($input);

my $reversed = reverse_string($input);
print "Reversed string: $reversed\n";
```

To run this script:

1. Save it to a file, for example, `reverse_string.pl`.
2. Make sure you have Perl installed on your system.
3. Run the script using the command: `perl reverse_string.pl`
4. Enter the string you wish to reverse when prompted. The script will then output the reversed string.
